\ul Hardware System Notes:\ulnone \
\
Sensors
\f1\b0  - sensors are attached via cable to the microcontroller. The cables have four wires, which must be connected in the right order for the sensors to function. In short, one side of the cable end that is to be connected to a sensor (socket/female) is solid black, whereas the other side has holes. \
\
The right side that is solid black should be connected to the GND (ground) of the sensor (see picture below).\
\
