\ul Software System Notes:\ulnone \
\
System On/Off
\f1\b0  - Toggles whether the system is on (reading in sensor data, making sound) or off
\f0\b \
\
Largest Distance
\f1\b0  - Set to just below distance from sensor to wall - use Raw data output below to determine that value\
\

\f0\b Movement Range
\f1\b0  - Set to the highest amount of movement - can usually just keep at default, but if system is not responsive, make lower; if system is too sensitive to movement, make higher\
\

\f0\b Movement Threshold
\f1\b0  - Determines the value below which the system is in a state of not having a person in the tunnel - above triggers when the sound turns on. Shouldn\'92t have to change.\
\

\f0\b Trigger Threshold
\f1\b0  - Value at which discrete sounds (\'93hits\'94) will be triggered}